The Isochrone algorithm returns service/reachability areas for multiple locations and time/distance ranges.

You need to have a valid API key ('Web' menu ► 'ORS Tools' ► 'Configuration') or sign up at <a href="https://openrouteservice.org/sign-up/">https://openrouteservice.org/sign-up/</a>.

As Geometry Input, choose a Point from the map.

The ranges parameter needs to be a comma-separated list of integer values, no decimal points. Current restriction limits apply, see https://openrouteservice.org/restrictions/.

The output layer is a Polygon layer with ID, range value, travel mode and total population (from <a href="https://ghsl.jrc.ec.europa.eu/about.php">GHSL</a>). The CRS is EPSG:4326.